<p id="para0018">For each tip on a rooted bifurcating (time interval bootstrap) tree, the viral lineage-level diversification rate (
 <italic>DR
  <sub>i</sub>
 </italic>) was calculated as the reciprocal sum of 
 <italic>N
  <sub>i</sub>
 </italic> branch lengths (
 <italic>l
  <sub>j</sub>)
 </italic> from tip 
 <italic>i</italic> to the root, with each consecutive edge (
 <italic>j)</italic> down-weighted by a factor of 1⁄2 
 <xref rid="bib0012" ref-type="bibr">[12]</xref>.
 <disp-formula id="ueqn0001">
